To get System $B$ from System $A$, we need to replace the first equation with the sum of both equations from System $A$:

System $A$ | $\text{\quad}$ | System $B$
:-: | :-: | :-:
$\begin{cases}\blueD{6x-5y=1}\\\\\goldD{-2x+2y=-1}\end{cases}$ || $\begin{cases}\maroonD{4x-3y=0}\\\\\goldD{-2x+2y=-1}\end{cases}$

$\begin{array}{r}
\blueD{\phantom{-}6x-5y=\phantom{-}1}
\\
\underline{{}+(\goldD{-2x+2y=-1}\rlap )}
\\
\maroonD{\phantom{-}4x-3y=\phantom{-}0}
\end{array}$

To get System $B$ from System $A$, we need to replace the second equation with the difference of both equations from System $A$:

System $A$ | $\text{\quad}$ | System $B$
:-: | :-: | :-:
$\begin{cases}\blueD{5x+y=3}\\\\\goldD{4x-7y=8}\end{cases}$ || $\begin{cases}\blueD{5x+y=3}\\\\\maroonD{x+8y=-5}\end{cases}$

$\begin{array}{r}
\blueD{\phantom{}5x+\phantom{7}y=\phantom{-}3}
\\
\underline{{}-(\goldD{4x-7y=\phantom{-}8}\rlap )}
\\
\maroonD{\phantom{-}x+8y=\phantom{}-5}
\end{array}$

To get System $B$ from System $A$, we need to replace the second equation with the sum of both equations from System $A$:

System $A$ | $\text{\quad}$ | System $B$
:-: | :-: | :-:
$\begin{cases}\blueD{-4x-6y=9}\\\\\goldD{3x+y=-4}\end{cases}$ || $\begin{cases}\blueD{-4x-6y=9}\\\\\maroonD{-x-5y=5}\end{cases}$

$\begin{array}{r}
\blueD{\phantom{}-4x-\phantom{}6y=\phantom{-}9}
\\
\underline{{}+(\phantom{-}\goldD{3x+\phantom{6}y=\phantom{}-4}\rlap )}
\\
\maroonD{\phantom{}-x-5y=\phantom{-}5}
\end{array}$

To get System $B$ from System $A$, we need to replace only the left-hand side of the first equation with the sum of the left-hand sides of both equations (notice that the right-hand sides stay the same):

System $A$ | $\text{\quad}$ | System $B$
:-: | :-: | :-:
$\begin{cases}\blueD{x+3y}=-9\\\\\goldD{2x+y}=4\end{cases}$ || $\begin{cases}\maroonD{3x+4y}=-9\\\\\goldD{2x+y}=4\end{cases}$

$\begin{array}{r}
\blueD{\phantom{}x+\phantom{}3y}
\\
\underline{{}+(\phantom{}\goldD{2x+\phantom{6}y}\rlap )}
\\
\maroonD{\phantom{}3x+4y}
\end{array}$
